parameters.name:
client_id

This
parameters.description: is is the OAuth client_id value. This is one of the OAuth values that you get from your eBay account manager (the other value is the client_secret ).

parameters.name:
redirect_uri

This
parameters.description: value is used to authenticate your application. Enter the RuName value for either the Sandbox or Production environment, depending on the environment you intend to target.

parameters.name:
response_type

This
parameters.description: value must be set to code to have eBay generate and return an authorization code .

parameters.name:
scope

This
parameters.description: is is a list of OAuth scopes. Each REST operation has one or more scopes; refer to the API Reference to find the scope(s) required for each call. If you need to use multiple scopes, separate the scopes in the string with URL-encoded spaces. The example request above uses two scopes.

parameters.name:
state

An
parameters.description:
opaque value used by the client to maintain state between the request and callback. The authorization server includes this value when redirecting the user-agent back to the client, and the same value supplied in the call is returned in the response.

While this value is optional, we recommend you supply a state value to prevent cross-site request forgery, as described in Section 10.12 of the OAuth spec.

parameters.name: If
parameters.description:
the SKU field is returned.

This indicates this listing is for a specific item within a group. To get the RESTful item Id of the item, pass in the ItemID and SKU values in using the Get Item by Legacy Id call in the Browse API.

browse/v1/item/get_item_by_legacy_id?legacy_item_id=110039490209&legacy_variation_sku=V-00031-WHM

parameters.name: If
parameters.description:
the SKU field is not returned.
This indicates this listing is for a specific item, which in not part of a group. To get the RESTful item Id, pass in the itemID value using the Get Item by Legacy Id call in the Browse API.


browse/v1/item/get_item_by_legacy_id?legacy_item_id=110039490209
